ge":"en-US","@id":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/#/schema/logo/image/","url":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/default.jpg","contentUrl":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/default.jpg","width":630,"height":630,"caption":"Piping Pot Curry"},"image":{"@id":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/#/schema/logo/image/"},"sameAs":["https://www.facebook.com/pipingpotcurry","https://x.com/pipingpotcurry","https://www.instagram.com/pipingpotcurry/","https://www.pinterest.com/pipingpotcurry/","https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC929bqkJli6q9GGha87rvig","https://www.linkedin.com/company/piping-pot-curry/","https://www.tiktok.com/@pipingpotcurry/"]},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/#/schema/person/5af3bb5d23da48beaa3bf3905d059836","name":"Meeta Arora","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/#/schema/person/image/","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1311cfb95e39c421955576dcd7dd440709dd5d069f33dd03f9b665b9f75e91c9?s=96&d=blank&r=g","contentUrl":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1311cfb95e39c421955576dcd7dd440709dd5d069f33dd03f9b665b9f75e91c9?s=96&d=blank&r=g","caption":"Meeta Arora"},"description":"I strongly believe that each one of us has a chef inside us, we just need to explore the ingredients and create great food. My passion is to share easy, and wholesome recipes made using Instant Pot &amp; Air Fryer, that are well tested, so you can cook with confidence.","sameAs":["https://pipingpotcurry.com/meeta-arora/","https://www.facebook.com/pipingpotcurry/","https://www.instagram.com/pipingpotcurry/","https://www.linkedin.com/in/meetaarora/","https://www.pinterest.com/pipingpotcurry/","https://x.com/pipingpotcurry","https://www.youtube.com/c/pipingpotcurry"]},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#faq-question-1630505072244","position":1,"url":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#faq-question-1630505072244","name":"Where can I buy modak mold?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"I got the aluminum modak mold from the Indian grocery store. They are also available on <a data-eafl-id=\"14657\" data-eafl-text=\"Amazon\" href=\"https://amzn.to/2Ya2QYb\" class=\"eafl-link\">Amazon</a>. If you don't have the mold, then you can still make the modak using the hands modak method detailed above.","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#faq-question-1630505137153","position":2,"url":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#faq-question-1630505137153","name":"How to serve ukadiche modak?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"These modak are best served warm with a drizzle of ghee on top. Top with about a teaspoon of ghee. ","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#faq-question-1630505342708","position":3,"url":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#faq-question-1630505342708","name":"How to store steamed modak?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"These modaks stay fresh for 1 day at room temperature and a couple of days in the refrigerator. We prefer to enjoy the modak while it is still warm. It tastes so good!","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#faq-question-1630505643668","position":4,"url":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#faq-question-1630505643668","name":"How to reheat modak?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Steam them for 3-4 minutes to reheat the stored modak. Enjoy warm! ","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"Ukadiche Modak (steamed rice dumplings with sweet coconut filling)","author":{"@id":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/#/schema/person/5af3bb5d23da48beaa3bf3905d059836"},"description":"Ukadiche Modak is an Indian sweet dumpling made during the festival of Ganesh Chaturthi. It is made from steamed rice flour and stuffed with a sweet mixture of jaggery and grated coconut.","datePublished":"2022-08-14T07:16:29+00:00","image":["https://pipingpotcurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Ukadiche-Modak-Piping-Pot-Curry.jpg","https://pipingpotcurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Ukadiche-Modak-Piping-Pot-Curry-500x500.jpg","https://pipingpotcurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Ukadiche-Modak-Piping-Pot-Curry-500x375.jpg","https://pipingpotcurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Ukadiche-Modak-Piping-Pot-Curry-480x270.jpg"],"video":{"name":"Ukadiche Modak (using a mold)","description":"Ukadiche Modak is an Indian sweet dumpling made during the festival of Ganesh Chaturthi. It is made from steamed rice flour and stuffed with a sweet mixture of jaggery and grated coconut.","thumbnailUrl":"https://content.jwplatform.com/thumbs/Gu9oxxhd-720.jpg","contentUrl":"https://content.jwplatform.com/videos/Gu9oxxhd.mp4","uploadDate":"2021-09-11T00:05:44.000Z","@type":"VideoObject"},"recipeYield":["12"],"prepTime":"PT40M","cookTime":"PT15M","totalTime":"PT55M","recipeIngredient":["1 cup Grated Coconut (fresh or frozen (see notes))","3/4 cup Jaggery (grated or broken in to small pieces )","1/4 teaspoon Cardamom powder (Elaichi)","1 tablespoon Poppy Seeds (Khus khus) (roasted)","1 cup Water","2 teaspoon Ghee (divided)","1/4 teaspoon Salt  ((optional))","1 cup  Rice flour (very fine (see notes))","Saffron ((optional))"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Prepare the filling:","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Heat a heavy bottom pan on medium flame. Add the grated coconut and roast it for 2-3 minutes.","name":"Heat a heavy bottom pan on medium flame. Add the grated coconut and roast it for 2-3 minutes.","url":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#wprm-recipe-10740-step-0-0","image":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Ukadiche-Modak-Steps-Piping-Pot-Curry-1.jpg"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add jaggery, cardamom and poppy seeds. Cook until they blend together and ooze out a little liquid, about 2-3 minutes. Do not overcook.","name":"Add jaggery, cardamom and poppy seeds. Cook until they blend together and ooze out a little liquid, about 2-3 minutes. Do not overcook.","url":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#wprm-recipe-10740-step-0-1","image":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Ukadiche-Modak-Steps-Piping-Pot-Curry-2.jpg"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Take the pan off the flame and let it cool. It is important that the mixture completely cools.","name":"Take the pan off the flame and let it cool. It is important that the mixture completely cools.","url":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#wprm-recipe-10740-step-0-2","image":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Ukadiche-Modak-Steps-Piping-Pot-Curry-3.jpg"}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Prepare the covering:","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"In a pot, bring 1 cup of water to a rolling boil. Add 1 tsp ghee and salt (optional).","name":"In a pot, bring 1 cup of water to a rolling boil. Add 1 tsp ghee and salt (optional).","url":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#wprm-recipe-10740-step-1-0","image":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Ukadiche-Modak-Steps-Piping-Pot-Curry-4.jpg"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add the rice flour, mix it well with a spoon. This will make a lumpy dough. Turn off the flame. Cover the pot and leave it for 3-5 minutes.","name":"Add the rice flour, mix it well with a spoon. This will make a lumpy dough. Turn off the flame. Cover the pot and leave it for 3-5 minutes.","url":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#wprm-recipe-10740-step-1-1","image":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Ukadiche-Modak-Steps-Piping-Pot-Curry-5.jpg"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Remove this to a large bowl and let it cool a bit. You want this mixture to be still warm while you make a dough from it.","name":"Remove this to a large bowl and let it cool a bit. You want this mixture to be still warm while you make a dough from it.","url":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#wprm-recipe-10740-step-1-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"While the mixture is still warm, apply some ghee and warm water to your hands and knead it until it is soft, about 5-7 minutes. The dough should not look patchy or crumble. You will need to add about 2 tablespoons of warm water while kneading to make a smooth dough. Optionally, you can also add couple of teaspoons of warm milk while kneading the dough which will make it extra soft.","name":"While the mixture is still warm, apply some ghee and warm water to your hands and knead it until it is soft, about 5-7 minutes. The dough should not look patchy or crumble. You will need to add about 2 tablespoons of warm water while kneading to make a smooth dough. Optionally, you can also add couple of teaspoons of warm milk while kneading the dough which will make it extra soft.","url":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#wprm-recipe-10740-step-1-3","image":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Ukadiche-Modak-Steps-Piping-Pot-Curry-1-2.jpg"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Wrap the dough with a damp cloth. It is important to keep the dough damp and soft. Now make 12 lemon size balls. Note: The size of the balls will also depend on the size of the modak mold you have. Also keep the balls covered with the damp cloth.","name":"Wrap the dough with a damp cloth. It is important to keep the dough damp and soft. Now make 12 lemon size balls. Note: The size of the balls will also depend on the size of the modak mold you have. Also keep the balls covered with the damp cloth.","url":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#wprm-recipe-10740-step-1-4","image":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Ukadiche-Modak-Steps-Piping-Pot-Curry-8.jpg"}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Assembling Modak:","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Apply some ghee or oil to the base of a steamer basket.","name":"Apply some ghee or oil to the base of a steamer basket.","url":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#wprm-recipe-10740-step-2-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Open the mold and apply ghee with your fingers to the inside of the mold. Close the mold, and place one lemon size dough ball inside the mold.","name":"Open the mold and apply ghee with your fingers to the inside of the mold. Close the mold, and place one lemon size dough ball inside the mold.","url":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#wprm-recipe-10740-step-2-1","image":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Ukadiche-Modak-Steps-Piping-Pot-Curry-9.jpg"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Now with your finger start spreading the dough to the sides of the mold so it gets the shape. Allow some dough to come out of the mold which will be used to seal after adding the stuffing.","name":"Now with your finger start spreading the dough to the sides of the mold so it gets the shape. Allow some dough to come out of the mold which will be used to seal after adding the stuffing.","url":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#wprm-recipe-10740-step-2-2","image":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Ukadiche-Modak-Steps-Piping-Pot-Curry-10.jpg"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Scoop in a spoonful of the filling and gently seal the bottom with the dough that came out of the mold.","name":"Scoop in a spoonful of the filling and gently seal the bottom with the dough that came out of the mold.","url":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#wprm-recipe-10740-step-2-3","image":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Ukadiche-Modak-Steps-Piping-Pot-Curry-11.jpg"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Open the mold and remove the modak gently. Place it in a steamer basket. Make remaining modak&#039;s in the same way. Between making modak&#039;s, apply ghee again to the mold.","name":"Open the mold and remove the modak gently. Place it in a steamer basket. Make remaining modak&#039;s in the same way. Between making modak&#039;s, apply ghee again to the mold.","url":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#wprm-recipe-10740-step-2-4","image":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Ukadiche-Modak-Steps-Piping-Pot-Curry-13.jpg"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Optionally, place a strand of saffron on top of each modak and press it into the rice flour covering.","name":"Optionally, place a strand of saffron on top of each modak and press it into the rice flour covering.","url":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#wprm-recipe-10740-step-2-5","image":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Ukadiche-Modak-Steps-Piping-Pot-Curry-14.jpg"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Depending on the size of your steamer basket, you might want to steam modak in multiple batches. You want to make sure the modak are not placed too close to each other.","name":"Depending on the size of your steamer basket, you might want to steam modak in multiple batches. You want to make sure the modak are not placed too close to each other.","url":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#wprm-recipe-10740-step-2-6"}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Steaming Modak in the stovetop steamer:","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"In a pot where the steamer basket fits, bring water to a rolling boil. Set the boiling water on medium heat. Place the steamer basket and steam the modak covered for 8-10 minutes. You should see a shine appear on the modak.","name":"In a pot where the steamer basket fits, bring water to a rolling boil. Set the boiling water on medium heat. Place the steamer basket and steam the modak covered for 8-10 minutes. You should see a shine appear on the modak.","url":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#wprm-recipe-10740-step-3-0","image":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Ukadiche-Modak-ready-to-be-steamed-Piping-Pot-Curry.jpg"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Take the steamer basket out and let it cool for about 5 minutes. This will help make sure the base does not break when you pick up the modak.","name":"Take the steamer basket out and let it cool for about 5 minutes. This will help make sure the base does not break when you pick up the modak.","url":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#wprm-recipe-10740-step-3-1"}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Steaming Modak in the Instant Pot:","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add 1 cup of water to the Instant Pot insert and place the trivet. Let the water boil on saute mode while you are preparing the modak.","name":"Add 1 cup of water to the Instant Pot insert and place the trivet. Let the water boil on saute mode while you are preparing the modak.","url":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#wprm-recipe-10740-step-4-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Place the steamer basket with modak on the trivet. Close lid with valve in venting position. Set on steam mode and steam for 10 minutes. You will need an external timer to keeo the time.","name":"Place the steamer basket with modak on the trivet. Close lid with valve in venting position. Set on steam mode and steam for 10 minutes. You will need an external timer to keeo the time.","url":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#wprm-recipe-10740-step-4-1","image":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Ukadiche-Modak-steaming-in-instant-pot-Piping-Pot-Curry.jpg"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"After 10 minutes, remove the lid after the pin has dropped. Carefully remove the steamer basket and let the modak cool for about 5 minutes. This will help make sure the base does not break when you pick up the modak.","name":"After 10 minutes, remove the lid after the pin has dropped. Carefully remove the steamer basket and let the modak cool for about 5 minutes. This will help make sure the base does not break when you pick up the modak.","url":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#wprm-recipe-10740-step-4-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Ukadiche Modak is ready to be enjoyed!","name":"Ukadiche Modak is ready to be enjoyed!","url":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#wprm-recipe-10740-step-4-3"}]}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"4.93","ratingCount":"13","reviewCount":"4"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Hello Meeta\r\n\r\nI made these today as first day Ganpati prasad. They were a massive hit. An old lady I met said she had been coming to the temple for 8 years and this is the first time she’s had modaks this delicious and gorgeous looking (I did the traditional hand pleating of the covering)\r\n\r\nAnother lady asked if I take orders. \r\n\r\nI just smiled and gave them the links to your recipe. \r\n\r\nGetting all the appreciation made my day. Hope reading about it makes yours too! \r\n\r\nGanpati bappa morya!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Pallavi Verma"},"datePublished":"2023-09-19"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Thank you for another great recipe. Tried these modaks for Ganesh Chaturthi today and they were awesome. The video and detailed step by step recipe really helped.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Sheetu"},"datePublished":"2022-08-31"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Meeta - the modaks turned out great. I made it in the Instant Pot and they were perfectly cooked. The step by step pictures really helped.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Anushree Shetty"},"datePublished":"2020-08-22"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"They look delicious..can't wait for next Ganesh chaturthi to try them out!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Shweta"},"datePublished":"2019-09-03"}],"recipeCategory":["Dessert"],"recipeCuisine":["Indian"],"keywords":"ukadiche modak","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"160 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"25 g","proteinContent":"1 g","fatContent":"6 g","saturatedFatContent":"5 g","cholesterolContent":"2 mg","sodiumContent":"52 mg","fiberContent":"2 g","sugarContent":"13 g","servingSize":"1 serving"},"@id":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https://pipingpotcurry.com/ukadiche-modak/"}]}</script>
